4. praetoris urna: the urn into which the ballots of the iudices were cast. Itis fallax, since it gives an unjust verdict‚ either because a false return of the votes has been made by the praetor, or because he has influenced the iudices to make a wrong decision. Each iudex was given three tab- lets‚ inscribed with A (absolvo), c (condemno), N. L. (non liquet), respectively‚ one oi which he east into the urm-vicerit: Intr. 43.
